Text: What we achieved.
This week was a continuation of the work we did last week.
We met once as a group in person and had a zoom session with Eric to go over the work we had done so far.
Me and Roro also met up twice to do some pair programming stuff to sort out the final bits of our pipeline.
The good.
The group has hit a good rhythm and I feel we are continuing to improve on team communication.
Having regular team meetings has meant we are more aware of what each of us are doing.
We have managed to get most of the work we needed to get done for the project and only need to add in a few finishing touches to get the project done.
I feel I have improvedÂ  from the previous weeks in terms of coding, working much faster using python.
I've definitely had moments where I have very inefficient and slow but I have realised I have improved my skills since the start of the project.
Things to improve on as a team.
I would say this week has been the best week so far and we have gotten into a good groove of knowing what we need to do.
We could probably continue to even be more communicative with each other during times we are not meeting, by possibly sending messages to the group letting them know what we have been working on.
We will also have to make sure we have plenty of time to prepare for the final presentation and cover each section that is required to be presented.
To do this, we will need to divide up the sections among the team and have time to double check our slides before Friday.
Things I could do better.
I feel I did a better job of keeping in touch with team member individually and making sure to know what they were working on.
The main thing I will need to do this last week, is to keep focused and make sure I help the team as much as I can for the final presentation.
Goals for next week.
Most of next week will be spent writing the report as we are mostly finishing up our work over the weekend.
Our team goals will be to finish everything off and make sure we are ready for the final presentation.
General thoughtsÂ .
The biggest lessons from this studio project have been the understanding of how different personalities work and how to best fit my skills and strengths to help the team.
I feel in this project I have to had to be a bit more assertive in terms of organising the team, as some of my teammates would be happy working at length by themselves.

Going into the last project, I will have a better awareness that my next group may operate in a completely different manner to this one and I should not go in expecting it to operate in the same manner as my previous experiences.
This project has also taught me that I should be a bit more assertive in contributing my own ideas even if I feel like I am less technically competent as other people.
This means being open to discuss different ideas to come up with a ideal solutions as opposed to going with an idea simply based on who is saying it.
The level of stress in this project has been minimal and the main problem has been making sure I do enough to feel I have contributed to the project.
My team mates have seemed quite calm, which has been beneficial for my expectations of how stressed I should be.
This has shown me that stress can be an infectious trait.
If your team mates are overly stressed, then that can infect your own behaviour making the the experience much less enjoyable and not adding to the quality of the work.

I feel that the only real ways to mitigate these things is to do lots of research before implementing solutions and being organised so that everything is clearly outlined in terms of who is doing what.
I've also noticed sometimes we can get caught up on what we personally want as opposed to having a consideration of how to be effective for the team.
Our own ego's can get the best of us, pulling us into directions based on our own desires.

There will be people who we may not get along with or ideas thatÂ  we are not a fan of, but there is virtue in working out these difference in creating something greater than what we could do ourselves.
Hopefully, I've done enough to help out the team the best I can.
Overall
